* def roundAwayFromZero =
29
function(value, decimalPlaces) { // Ensure value is a number var num = Number(value); if (isNaN(num)) { return num; // Return as is if it's not a valid number } var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces); var valueToRound = num * factor; var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : Math.round(valueToRound); return roundedValue / factor; }

* def roundAwayFromZero =
1
function(value, decimalPlaces) { // Ensure value is a number var num = Number(value); if (isNaN(num)) { return num; // Return as is if it's not a valid number } var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces); var valueToRound = num * factor; var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : Math.round(valueToRound); return roundedValue / factor; }

* def roundAwayFromZero =
3
function(value, decimalPlaces) { // Ensure value is a number var num = Number(value); if (isNaN(num)) { return num; // Return as is if it's not a valid number } var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces); var valueToRound = num * factor; var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : Math.round(valueToRound); return roundedValue / factor; }

* def roundAwayFromZero =
0
function(value, decimalPlaces) { // Ensure value is a number var num = Number(value); if (isNaN(num)) { return num; // Return as is if it's not a valid number } var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces); var valueToRound = num * factor; var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : Math.round(valueToRound); return roundedValue / factor; }

function(value, decimalPlaces) { // Ensure value is a number var num = Number(value); if (isNaN(num)) { return num; // Return as is if it's not a valid number } var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces); var valueToRound = num * factor; var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : Math.round(valueToRound); return roundedValue / factor; }

function(value, decimalPlaces) { // Ensure value is a number var num = Number(value); if (isNaN(num)) { return num; // Return as is if it's not a valid number } var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces); var valueToRound = num * factor; var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : Math.round(valueToRound); return roundedValue / factor; }

function(value, decimalPlaces) { // Ensure value is a number var num = Number(value); if (isNaN(num)) { return num; // Return as is if it's not a valid number } var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces); var valueToRound = num * factor; var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : Math.round(valueToRound); return roundedValue / factor; }

function(value, decimalPlaces) { // Ensure value is a number var num = Number(value); if (isNaN(num)) { return num; // Return as is if it's not a valid number } var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces); var valueToRound = num * factor; var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : Math.round(valueToRound); return roundedValue / factor; }

function(value, decimalPlaces) { // Ensure value is a number var num = Number(value); if (isNaN(num)) { return num; // Return as is if it's not a valid number } var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces); var valueToRound = num * factor; var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : Math.round(valueToRound); return roundedValue / factor; }

(valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : Math.round(valueToRound); return roundedValue / factor; }

function(value, decimalPlaces) { // Ensure value is a number var num = Number(value); if (isNaN(num)) { return num; // Return as is if it's not a valid number } var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces); var valueToRound = num * factor; var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : Math.round(valueToRound); return roundedValue / factor; }

function(value, decimalPlaces) { // Ensure value is a number var num = Number(value); if (isNaN(num)) { return num; // Return as is if it's not a valid number } var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces); var valueToRound = num * factor; var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : Math.round(valueToRound); return roundedValue / factor; }

function(value, decimalPlaces) { // Ensure value is a number var num = Number(value); if (isNaN(num)) { return num; // Return as is if it's not a valid number } var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces); var valueToRound = num * factor; var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : Math.round(valueToRound); return roundedValue / factor; }

function(value, decimalPlaces) { // Ensure value is a number var num = Number(value); if (isNaN(num)) { return num; // Return as is if it's not a valid number } var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces); var valueToRound = num * factor; var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : Math.round(valueToRound); return roundedValue / factor; }

function(value, decimalPlaces) { // Ensure value is a number var num = Number(value); if (isNaN(num)) { return num; // Return as is if it's not a valid number } var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces); var valueToRound = num * factor; var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : Math.round(valueToRound); return roundedValue / factor; }

function(value, decimalPlaces) { // Ensure value is a number var num = Number(value); if (isNaN(num)) { return num; // Return as is if it's not a valid number } var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces); var valueToRound = num * factor; var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : Math.round(valueToRound); return roundedValue / factor; }

function(value, decimalPlaces) { // Ensure value is a number var num = Number(value); if (isNaN(num)) { return num; // Return as is if it's not a valid number } var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces); var valueToRound = num * factor; var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : Math.round(valueToRound); return roundedValue / factor; }

function(value, decimalPlaces) { // Ensure value is a number var num = Number(value); if (isNaN(num)) { return num; // Return as is if it's not a valid number } var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces); var valueToRound = num * factor; var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : Math.round(valueToRound); return roundedValue / factor; }

function(value, decimalPlaces) { // Ensure value is a number var num = Number(value); if (isNaN(num)) { return num; // Return as is if it's not a valid number } var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces); var valueToRound = num * factor; var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : Math.round(valueToRound); return roundedValue / factor; }

function(value, decimalPlaces) { // Ensure value is a number var num = Number(value); if (isNaN(num)) { return num; // Return as is if it's not a valid number } var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces); var valueToRound = num * factor; var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : Math.round(valueToRound); return roundedValue / factor; }

function(value, decimalPlaces) { // Ensure value is a number var num = Number(value); if (isNaN(num)) { return num; // Return as is if it's not a valid number } var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces); var valueToRound = num * factor; var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : Math.round(valueToRound); return roundedValue / factor; }

function(value, decimalPlaces) { // Ensure value is a number var num = Number(value); if (isNaN(num)) { return num; // Return as is if it's not a valid number } var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces); var valueToRound = num * factor; var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : Math.round(valueToRound); return roundedValue / factor; }

* def roundAwayFromZero =
0
function(value, decimalPlaces) { // Ensure value is a number var num = Number(value); if (isNaN(num)) { return num; // Return as is if it's not a valid number } var factor = Math.pow(10, decimalPlaces); var valueToRound = num * factor; var roundedValue = (valueToRound % 1 == 0.5 || valueToRound % 1 == -0.5) ? (valueToRound > 0 ? Math.floor(valueToRound) + 1 : Math.ceil(valueToRound) - 1) : Math.round(valueToRound); return roundedValue / factor; }
